<font color="#FF0000">TEACHING MY CHILDREN</font><br>
<tt>Sat Oct  4  1:46:12 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
  I have eighteen year old son and daughter and a fifteen year old son. I can't tell them what I did in the war. I can't even tell my wife. She found my accomidations one day so she has some idea. She knows that there are some  things that I can't talk about. <br>
  I have always felt that the army was good for me in helpping me mature. Some of the best times in my life happened in the army. As well as some of the worse. Do I want this for my children? No.  <br>
  I have taught them about patriottism, respect for our country and soldiers, an the good thinks about our life here. They also so have a duty to make this country better and to protect it. <br>
  I can not ask them to put their lives in jeopardy for a cause like Viet Nam. I'll suffer that war. I will not let my children suffer it if I can. They will make their own dissions and I will live with them. <br>
  The war lives in me every day. It won,t go away. What was it for?  It's for me to use as a tool to teach my children with. To teach them that a war like Viet Nam does very little good. Win, Lose or Draw people only suffer in the end.
